Description: UpdateLogic provides firmware updates for digital television receivers.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: UpdateLogic Incorporated provides firmware updates for digital television receivers in the United States. It offers UpdateTV software update service, which allows television (TV) manufacturers and cable TV operators to deliver software patches to consumer's digital television receiver devices, such as high definition television sets, cable boxes, and digital-to-analog converter boxes. The company's UpdateTV allows in delivering critical software and firmware updates through traditional terrestrial digital signals, in-band distribution via standard digital cable networks, or through the Internet to connected television devices. Its UpdateTV also enables consumer electronics manufacturers to automatically distribute software updates and other data to their digital televisions devices. The company also provides netReady services suite for Internet TVs and other Internet-enabled consumer electronic devices, including set-top boxes and Blu-ray players. It provides services and infrastructure to test, package, schedule, and deliver filmware updates to digital television devices. The company also sends television software or firmware patches through the air directly to digital televisions or digital-to-analog converters for transparent updates. UpdateLogic Incorporated was formerly known as Broadcast Data Corporation. The company was founded in 2003 and is based in Southborough, Massachusetts.

Description: Crystal Innovations develops the Flash Crystal, which is a device that can be used to initiate the wireless transfer of various media types
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: At Crystal Innovations Inc, we believe that music should be easily accessible for the listener and financially beneficial for the artist. We also believe in building authentic relationships between artists and their audience. In comes Flash Crystal. Flash Crystals are small, portable, crystal devices that can be used to initiate the wireless transfer of various types of media including music, documents, photos, portfolios, and direct contact information. Flash Crystals are connected to your keychain so you will never be without your music. They never run out of power and can be used an infinite number of times to share your music. They are extremely durable and will not break or crack. Flash Crystals offer artists the opportunity to instantly build rapport with potential fans. Our research has shown that it is much easier for artists to build fan bases using Flash Crystal because of its novelty. The process of explaining the new technology and showing how it works, will give the artist a better chance of getting their music heard/purchased simply because the potential fan now has vested interest in the product. The Flash Crystal gives artists a huge promotional advantage by allowing them to change the media on their device even after it is distributed into the market. To update your existing Flash Crystals with new media, artists would have to contact us directly for a simple reprogram and the new information is installed remotely.  Flash Crystals can be enabled to have their usage analytics downloaded for royalty disbursement and also for market research purposes. The possibility of piracy is also reduced as the music is stored online and only accessible through the Flash Crystal using Near Field Communication (NFC).  Flash Crystals can also be tracked every time it is used with its location, date of use and type of device it is shared with. Artists and their management teams can now improve their ability to keep track of the reach of their music and determine plans for increased exposure.

While they can take standard psychostimulants, up to 64% of patients either don't take them or stop taking them due to poor efficacy, side effects and high cost. Drug shortages are also common given that 10% of US children have ADHD and the number is rising rapidly (66% increase over 10 years). AdapTac has developed an education-based solution: a series of mobile and online strategy/action video games that build practice of attention and planning into fun games.

Description: APPMARX is a social networking service that enables website owners to network with contextual platforms.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: APPMARX is a Site Networking service.  APPMARX is structured as a social network, and used by site owners to "network" with contextual sites.  The APPMARX service is visible with participating site using a special recommendation widget. Key attributes of APPMARX Site Networking: 1. Oragnic: APPMARX provides contextual recommendations to users visiting a site. APPMARX is not a destination site. APPMARX is a network curated by site owners. 2. Human Curated Context: APPMARX is not using algorithms to produce context. It is deriving context from relationships between its participating sites. Overtime, relationships are curated by site owners based on what has been working best for their users.  For that APPMARX provides extensive statistical information of traffic behavior. 3. Social Mechanics: APPMARX leverages social mechanics to produce scalable site to site network. Site owners simply network with each other to produce connections that result with on-site recommendations. We believe that recommendations driven by site owners creates a fantastic contextual discovery graph for users. We call it 'Site Networking' because it's where site owners "network" in a new, meaningful way.
Founders: Adam Ben Ayoun, Tzachi Ben Ayoun
